        SCSS (Complete Notes)
1. What is SCSS

SCSS (Sassy CSS) is an extension of CSS that adds powerful programming-like features such as variables, nesting, mixins, and functions. It makes writing and managing large CSS files easier.

SCSS is part of SASS (Syntactically Awesome Style Sheets).
SCSS syntax is almost the same as CSS.
It must be compiled into normal CSS before the browser can read it.

Example:

SCSS

$color: red;

h1{
  color: $color;
}

Compiled CSS

h1{
  color:red;
}
2. Why SCSS is Used

When CSS becomes large in big projects, it becomes difficult to maintain.

SCSS solves this problem by providing:

Variables
Nesting
Mixins
Inheritance
Functions
Modular code structure

Benefits:

Cleaner code
Reusable styles
Easier maintenance
Faster development
3. Difference Between CSS and SCSS
CSS	SCSS
Plain styling language	CSS preprocessor
No variables	Supports variables
No nesting	Supports nesting
Repetition of code	Reusable code
Hard to maintain large files	Easy to manage large projects
4. Installing SCSS

Install using Node.js (npm)

npm install -g sass

Compile SCSS file:

sass style.scss style.css

Watch mode:

sass --watch style.scss:style.css
5. SCSS Variables

Variables store reusable values like colors, fonts, or spacing.

Syntax:

$variableName: value;

Example:

$primaryColor: blue;

h1{
 color:$primaryColor;
}

Advantages:

Avoid repeating values
Easy theme changes
6. Nesting in SCSS

SCSS allows writing CSS in a nested structure similar to HTML.

Example HTML

<nav>
  <ul>
    <li>Home</li>
  </ul>
</nav>

SCSS

nav{
  ul{
    list-style:none;
  }

  li{
    display:inline-block;
  }
}

Compiled CSS

nav ul{
 list-style:none;
}

nav li{
 display:inline-block;
}

This improves readability.

7. Partials in SCSS

Partials are smaller SCSS files used to organize code.

Example:

_variables.scss
_header.scss
_footer.scss

Import them into main file:

@import "variables";
@import "header";
8. Mixins

Mixins allow reusable blocks of CSS.

Syntax

@mixin name{
   styles
}

Example

@mixin center{
 display:flex;
 justify-content:center;
 align-items:center;
}

.box{
 @include center;
}

Output CSS

.box{
 display:flex;
 justify-content:center;
 align-items:center;
}
9. Inheritance (Extend)

SCSS allows sharing styles between selectors.

Example

.button{
 padding:10px;
 border-radius:5px;
}

.primary{
 @extend .button;
 background:blue;
}
10. Functions in SCSS

SCSS provides built-in functions for colors and math.

Example

$color: blue;

.box{
 background: darken($color,10%);
}

Other functions:

lighten()
darken()
rgba()
percentage()
11. Operators in SCSS

SCSS supports mathematical operations.

Example

.container{
 width:100% - 20%;
}

Operators:

+
-
*
/
%
12. SCSS File Structure (Best Practice)
scss/
  main.scss
  _variables.scss
  _header.scss
  _footer.scss
  _buttons.scss

Then import everything in main.scss.

13. SCSS Workflow

Developer writes:

style.scss

Compiler converts it into:

style.css

Browser only reads:

style.css
14. Real Example

SCSS

$primary: #3498db;

.card{
 background:$primary;
 padding:20px;

 h2{
   color:white;
 }

 button{
   background:white;
   color:$primary;
 }
}

Compiled CSS

.card{
 background:#3498db;
 padding:20px;
}

.card h2{
 color:white;
}

.card button{
 background:white;
 color:#3498db;
}
